page.title: 11Charing High Street Walk
page.content: If you walk down Charing High street today on your left you will see some houses where the butter used to be churned but now they are used as normal residential houses. Further down the High street you will see an inn called the King's Head. This used to be a cycle shop where people could get their bicycles and spares. Next to the pub is the electrician's. This used to be stables where people kept their horses when they weren't being used. On your left you will see the butchers. It is a very old building and has always been used as a butchers. Next on your right you will see the hair dresser's. It used to be a private house. Across the road from the hair dresser's you will see the Post Office. It is quite an old building and has always been a Post Office. CONT'D...
